rom\": 1218, \"to\": 1237}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is up to each IF and NOC to determine how to best serve their athletes and the global development of their sport,\\\" the IOC explains of the organisation's stance.\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1479, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1339, \"end\": 1342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.356904556985439e-15, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1437, \"end\": 1440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.972434907926869e-29, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their athletes\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1388}, {\"ngram\": \"the global development\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1415}, {\"ngram\": \"their sport\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1430}, {\"ngram\": \"the organisation's stance\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1478}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States Olympic and Paralympic Committee (USOPC) does provide prize money, with medal winners set to receive the same monetary rewards as in Tokyo at the last Summer Olympics.\", \"from\": 1481, \"to\": 1666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1485, \"end\": 1498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9922200901243179, \"rank\": 0.005137976523766271, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1632, \"end\": 1637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999923935009141, \"rank\": 7.605668546303927e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"USOPC\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1538}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1564}, {\"ngram\": \"medal winners\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1584}, {\"ngram\": \"the same monetary rewards\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1625}, {\"ngram\": \"the last Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1665}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold medallists will receive $37,500 (\\u00a329,300), silver medal winners $22,500 (\\u00a317,600) and third-placed finishers $15,000 (\\u00a311,700).\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1800, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gold medallists\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"silver medal winners\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1736}, {\"ngram\": \"third-placed finishers\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1781}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While most athletes have welcomed World Athletics' introduction of prize money, the move has been criticised in some quarters.\", \"from\": 1802, \"to\": 1928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1836, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.210176478278167e-16, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"most athletes\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 1821}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 1880}, {\"ngram\": \"the move\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1890}, {\"ngram\": \"some quarters\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 1927}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Five-time rowing gold medallist Steve Redgravesuggested that most Olympic sports would be unable to match the financial offering, potentially creating a \\\"two-tier\\\" system and dividing athletes.\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 2123, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Five-time rowing gold medallist Steve Redgravesuggested\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1985}, {\"ngram\": \"most Olympic sports\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2010}, {\"ngram\": \"the financial offering\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2058}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"two-tier\\\" system\", \"from\": 2081, \"to\": 2100}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2122}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If you win an Olympic gold medal in any athletics event, you are able to earn substantial financial gains from those results,\\\" Redgrave told theDaily Mail.\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2281, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an Olympic gold medal\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2158}, {\"ngram\": \"any athletics event\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2181}, {\"ngram\": \"substantial financial gains\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2231}, {\"ngram\": \"those results\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2250}, {\"ngram\": \"Redgrave\", \"from\": 2253, \"to\": 2261}, {\"ngram\": \"theDaily Mail\", \"from\": 2267, \"to\": 2280}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It smacks a bit hard for the sports that can not afford to do this.\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2351, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the sports\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2319}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rowing is in that situation.\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2380, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rowing\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2358}, {\"ngram\": \"that situation\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2379}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We struggle bringing sponsorship and finance into it.\", \"from\": 2381, \"to\": 2434, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sponsorship\", \"from\": 2402, \"to\": 2413}, {\"ngram\": \"finance\", \"from\": 2418, \"to\": 2425}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This separates the elite sports to the others like rowing, canoeing and most combat sports.\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2526, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phras